node.text: When we take care of people, we take care of the planet. We’re donating 100M disease-resistant coffee trees by 2025 to help farmers and their communities, and committing to reduce our landfill waste by 50% by 2030.

node.title: Caring for Our Planet & Our People

node.text: Why is Nitro Cold Brew so whoa? Bill Nye explains.

node.title: Bill Nye Presents Nitro Cold Brew

node.accessibility_caption: Two hands cheers an Iced Pumpkin Spice Latte and a Pumpkin Spice Frappuccino drink outside on a sunny day.
Eileen sits outside at a table with a Starbucks cup, laughing and wearing a shirt that says "strong like coffee."

node.text:
This summer, many of us daydreamed about what it would be like to be an Olympian. Eileen knows about the experience first-hand as an Olympic swimmer.

“I had the honor to represent Panama in three consecutive Olympic Games,” she says. “The most amazing feeling was walking into the Olympic Stadium carrying the flag and just that amazing feeling and honor to represent my country and every single Panamanian around the world.”

But Eileen says her “biggest and proudest title” is being a mom to her two sons. In this role, she represents Panama in a different way by passing her culture down to her kids.

“I feel a huge sense of pride knowing that both my children have their two identities as American, but also as Panamanian, that they are proud to be from Panama, that they are proud to speak the language…and that they are proud that they are part Latinos living in America.”

Join us for Latinx Heritage Month as we celebrate our Latinx partners (employees) and hear how they embrace their heritage, uphold important traditions and uplift our communities. #LatinxHeritageMonth
